How Sections, Filters, and Columns Work During View Creation
=============================================================

Phase 1: Initial Section Selection (during View Add)
-----------------------------------------------------

When you're in the View Properties/Add box (after F8 → INS or F10 View Add):

- The Section(s) field accepts a list of category names — each one becomes a
  section head.
- Press F3 (CHOICES) to pick from existing categories, or just type new
  category names.
- You can list multiple categories (e.g., Calls, Letters, Projects) — each
  becomes its own section.
- You can also set a view-level Filter right here (e.g., add "High Priority"
  to only show items assigned to that category across the whole view).
- Press ENTER to create the view. Agenda creates all sections at once, each
  with a default item column.

At this point the view exists but each section only has the item column — no
additional columns yet.


Phase 2: Adding Columns (after the view is created)
----------------------------------------------------

Columns are added per-section after the view exists:

1. Navigate to the section you want to modify
2. ALT-L (add column left) or ALT-R (add column right) — quick method
   - Or: F10 → View → Column → Add for full Column Add box with all settings
3. Enter/select a category for the column head (via F3 or typing)
4. The category type determines the column type:
   - Standard category → shows child category assignments
   - Date category (marked *) → shows dates/times
   - Numeric category (marked #) → shows numbers with optional calculations
   - Unindexed category → shows freeform text
5. Press ENTER


Phase 3: Setting Per-Section Filters and Properties
----------------------------------------------------

Each section can have its own filter independent of the view-level filter:

1. Highlight the section head
2. F6 (PROPS) — opens the Section Properties box
3. Key settings in this box:
   - Section head — change which category heads the section
   - Item sorting — how items sort within this section
   - Filter — section-level filter criteria:
     - Enter a standard category → opens Standard Filter Box → choose
       "Assigned" or "Not assigned"
     - Enter a date category → opens Date Filter Box → choose Assigned/Not
       assigned + optional date range
     - Enter a numeric category → opens Numeric Filter Box → choose value range
   - Columns — list of column head categories for this section (you can
     add/remove/reorder here too)
4. Press ENTER

Key insight: Items must pass BOTH the view-level filter AND the section-level
filter to appear. The section head itself is already an implicit filter — only
items assigned to that category appear in that section.


Concrete Keystroke Example: Full View Build
--------------------------------------------

F8                          → Open View Manager
INS                         → Add new view
Type "My Projects"          → Name the view
↓ to Section(s)             → Move to Section field
F3                          → Open category chooser
Select "ProjectA" → ENTER   → First section head
Type "ProjectB" → ENTER     → Second section head
ENTER                       → Create the view

(Now in the new view with two sections)

ALT-R                       → Add column to the right
F3 → select "When" → ENTER  → Date column added
ALT-R                       → Add another column
F3 → select "People" → ENTER → Standard column added

(Set a section-level filter)
Highlight "ProjectA" section head
F6                          → Open Section Properties
↓ to Filter                 → Move to Filter field
Type "High Priority"        → Filter category
  → Standard Filter Box opens
  → Choose "Assigned" → ENTER
ENTER                       → Save section properties
